        "exhibitionLabelText": {
            "en": {
                "purposes": [
                    "Sigg Online"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "Sigg Online",
                        "text": "This painting shows two miners risking their lives while mining for copper with pneumatic drills. The painting’s composition is well-structured and, done in Romantic style to dramatise the heroic behaviour of the miners and conquer danger. This painting is inspired by Wu’s travels to Red Hill in Urumqi, where, as an official painter, he personally witnessed the perilous life of miners. It points to the unparalleled passion Wu shared with the miners, and also shows how the aesthetics and ideological guidelines of realist art were employed by the state."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "zh-hant": {
                "purposes": [
                    "Sigg Online"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "Sigg Online",
                        "text": "畫中展示兩個礦工手持風鑽，奮不顧身地開採銅礦的情景。畫面結構工整，洋溢浪漫主義風格，並以戲劇化的形式呈現礦工面對危險時的英勇行為。這幅畫作的靈感，源自吳氏訪視烏魯木齊紅山的經歷，當時作為官方畫家的他，親眼目睹礦工嚴苛的生活環境。作品顯示他對礦工感同身受，也體現了現實主義藝術的美學和理念，是如何被國家運用。"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    },
